A thesis I read part of (forgot whose, but I might be able to find out)
used the HNA etch to remove p+ Si.  They reported a brown stain after
the etch, which they attributed to the presence of porous silicon.  To
remove the stain, they used 97:3 HNO3:HF (this is a Si etch) for 15 seconds.
FWIW, if your stain is, in fact, porous Si, the oxidation methods others
have mentioned should also work.

